We recommended that Management:
a. 	Apply or renew the registration of all serviceable motor vehicles with the LTO and contracts of insurance with the GSIS to ensure security and financial assurance in case of fortuitous events that may have an adverse effect on the said property;
b. 	Properly monitor the registration and insurance of all properties with the LTO and GSIS, respectively, to avoid payment of unnecessary penalties, surcharges and damages to third party liabilities in case of vehicular accidents;
c. 	Prepare and submit the Property Inventory Form (PIF) to GIF, GSIS, and to the Auditor, in compliance with COA Circular 2018-002; and
d. 	Submit to the Audit Team the list of unserviceable motor vehicles of the Municipality.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:
a. 	to conduct risk assessment;
b. 	to identify critical processes and functions;
c. 	to determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation;
d. 	to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis;
e. 	to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and
f. 	to submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.
Further, we recommended that members of the working group be capacitated by allowing them to attend seminars/trainings on the formulation of the PSCP.

We recommended that Management:
a. 	Ensure that the submitted GPB and GAD AR present regular PPAs of the LGU under the section, Attributed Programs, accompanied by the appropriate HGDG Checklist which is supported by relevant documents and means of verification to identify which part of the project cost/expenditure is attributable to the GAD Budget/Expenditure;
b. 	Report changes in the GPB to the DILG Regional Office pursuant to Item C.7.2 of the JMC;
c. 	 Ensure that the GAD M & E System of the LGU is in place and fully functional so as to assess the effectiveness and efficiency of their gender mainstreaming efforts; and
d. 	Strengthen and maintain GAD mechanisms instituted by the LGU to accelerate gender mainstreaming.

We recommended that Management:
a. 	Charge confidential expenses to appropriations for that purpose and properly record the same in the books as Confidential Expenses;
b. 	Stop the practice of paying confidential expenses thru reimbursement. Release confidential funds thru a cash advance duly supported by documents required per Sections 6.1.7 and 6.1.8 and drawn by a duly designated and bonded SDOs or HoA;
c. 	Observe the procedural guidelines outlined under Section 6.2 for the liquidation of the cash advance; and
d. 	Observe all other procedural guidelines and reporting requirements contained in DBM -DILG-DND-GCG-COA Joint Circular No. 2015-01 dated January 8, 2015 with respect to the disbursement of confidential funds.

Submit a document of authority such as Office Orders or Memoranda, indicating the names of persons who were assigned to COVID-19 facilities directly catering to or in contact with COVID-19 patients, PUIs, and PUMs, and the period of their assignment;
Strictly adhere to the provisions of RA No. 11469 of the “Bayanihan to Heal as One Act” and subsequent issuances relative thereof to address the needs on the national emergency arising from the COVID-19 pandemic; and
Support all transactions with valid, complete and proper documents as required under Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445 and COA Circular No. 2012-001.

Establish effective measures on logistics, storage and handling of all vaccine supplies to avoid spoilage and wastage;
Be transparent and accurate in reporting vaccine information especially regarding spoilage; and
Conduct a fact-finding investigation on the circumstances leading to the spoilage of vaccines and to impose administrative sanctions on those found liable.

