We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:
to conduct risk assessment;
to identify critical processes and functions;
to determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation;
to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis;
to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and
to submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.
Further, we recommended that members of the working group be capacitated by allowing them to attend seminars/trainings on the formulation of the PSCP.

We recommended that Management:
Present major/flagship programs/projects of the LGU under the section, Attributed Programs of the GAD Plan and Budget and the GAD Accomplishment Report and use the appropriate HGDG Checklist supported by relevant documents and means of verification to identify which part of the project cost/expenditure is attributable to the GAD Budget/Expenditure;
Capacitate the GAD Technical Working Group by allowing them to attend seminars/trainings on GAD especially on the use of the HGDG Tool;
Strictly observe the minimum allocation for GAD Budget/Expenditure which is five per cent of the total appropriations and maximize the utilization of the GAD funds through the identification and implementation of GAD-related programs and projects in order to attain the objectives for which funds were provided; and
Strictly observe the timelines in the submission of GPB and GAD AR to the Audit Team.

We recommended that Management, henceforth:

Require the concerned offices/units to properly categorize the in-kind donations received by the Municipality and intended for COVID-19 response to be reported in the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances for consolidation;

Require the concerned office to submit proof of receipt by and distribution to the beneficiaries as support to the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances for consolidation;

Require the LDRRMO to submit a consolidated report on Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances, separately for Cash and In-Kind transactions, to the NDRRMC through the OCD, copy furnished the Auditor, as required in COA Circular 2012-009;

Require the Property/Supply Officer to maintain Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM to properly account for the ending inventory balances; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements information pertaining to DRRM not evident on the face of the financial statements.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require:

The GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete LRNPCs for all roads and its components;

The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;

The Municipal Accountant to keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and reconcile the same with the LRNPCs and the result of the physical inventory taking at the end of each year; and

The Municipal Accountant to include the necessary disclosure on the total road network system of the LGU in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

We recommended that Management:

Present major/flagship programs/projects of the LGU under the section, Attributed Programs of the GAD Plan and Budget and the GAD Accomplishment Report;

Employ the HGDG tool for major/flagship programs/projects of the LGU and identify which part of the project cost/expenditure is attributable to the GAD Budget;

Maximize the utilization of the GAD funds through the identification and implementation of GAD-related programs and projects in order to attain the objectives for which funds were provided; and

